This article is a transcript of remarks made by Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and US President Donald Trump during a meeting in Tokyo. Prime Minister Abe expressed condolences for the recent shooting incident in Texas and expressed solidarity with the United States. He also welcomed President Trump's visit to Japan and mentioned the excitement among the Japanese people for Ivanka Trump's visit prior to that. The leaders discussed various issues including North Korea, trade, and military cooperation. President Trump thanked Prime Minister Abe for his hospitality and expressed gratitude for Japan's purchases of military equipment from the United States. Both leaders expressed their commitment to strengthening the Japan-US alliance. The meeting concluded with gratitude from President Trump for the relationship between the two countries.